[Update 04] Power Outage – North Carolina, South Carolina, Tennessee, Georgia | 07­05­22 | INC-#008675309

Date As Of: 07/05/2022 11:10	Sitrep Update #: 04
Incident Start Time: 07/01/2022
Incident End Time: Ongoing	Incident Location: NC, SC, TN, GA; U.S.
Impacted Sectors: Energy, (Electricity), Government Facilities, (Educational Facilities), Transportation Systems, (Aviation), (Highway and Motor Carrier), (Mass Transit and Passenger Rail), Water and Wastewater systems	Reported Cause: Targeted cyber incident on power substations surrounding Charlotte N.C., Greenville S.C., and Chattanooga T.N. 
Interagency Coordination: NSC/UCG	On Scene Agencies: DOE, FEMA

East Carolina Energy Corp

Incident Summary:

Background: 07/01/2022; 10:00 P.M: 
Simultaneous cyber incidents targeted substations controlled by East Carolina Energy Corp, Tennessee Local Electric, and SC Power LLC. Loss of control to substation monitoring networks and high heat conditions throughout the region created unstable electric grid regions and led to physical destruction of electric grid components throughout North Carolina, South Carolina, Tennessee, and Georgia. 

Source: CISA Region 4, FEMA Region 4, Department of Energy, FEMA National Watch Center, Federal Communications Commission, open source.


Update (as of 07/05/2022; 11:10): 
•	Utility companies have reported that they have regained control of computer networks
•	All listed owners/operators are working through long-term repairs to physical infrastructure supporting grid 

FEMA estimates that the power grid will be operational in the next 24-48 hours.

CRITICAL INFRASTRUCTURE INVOLVED:

ENERGY

(Electricity)

The Department of Energy reports approximately 5.1 million customers remain without power in North Carolina, South Carolina, Tennessee. Additionally, another 2.5 million electric customers in Georgia are reporting rolling blackouts and brownouts. 


GOVERNMENT FACILITIES

The Governors of North Carolina, South Carolina, Tennessee, and Georgia have all declared states of emergency. Local government offices are operating on generators, if available. (Education) All schools in affected states are closed. 


TRANSPORTATION SYSTEMS

(Highway and Motor Carrier)

Law enforcement is assisting circulation of traffic along roadways and intersections as traffic light and signal intervention outages continue across the island.

(National, Regional, and Local Rail Services)

All rail services in the region are currently non-operational.
